ZH: 一美元等于一百角。
EN: One dollar equals one hundred cents.

ZH: 这本书价格三十美元。
EN: This book costs thirty dollars.

ZH: 我只有一张五美元纸币。
EN: I only have a five dollar bill.

ZH: 他的薪水是以美元发放的。
EN: His salary is paid in dollars.

ZH: 旅行费用需要六百美元。
EN: The travel expenses amount to six hundred dollars.

ZH: 这栋房子售价两百万美元。
EN: The house is selling for two million dollars.

ZH: 你可以用信用卡支付美元账单。
EN: You can pay your dollar bill with a credit card.

ZH: 汇率是一美元兑换六点七人民币。
EN: The exchange rate is one dollar to six point seven Chinese yuan.

ZH: 我们的购买力减少了，美元不值那么多了。
EN: Our purchasing power has decreased, the dollar isn't worth as much anymore.

ZH: 昨天的汇率是一美元兑换七点五八港币。
EN: Yesterday's exchange rate was one dollar to seven point five eight Hong Kong dollars.

ZH: 这个包装箱里装着一万美元现金。
EN: There is ten thousand dollars in cash inside this package.

ZH: 美元是世界上最流行的货币之一。
EN: The dollar is one of the most popular currencies in the world.

ZH: 这份订单需要支付九千美元。
EN: This order requires a payment of nine thousand dollars.

ZH: 这家公司每月花费十万元美元。
EN: This company spends ten million dollars each month.

ZH: 他从银行取出了一束美元大钞。
EN: He withdrew a bundle of dollar bills from the bank.

ZH: 请用美元支付这笔账单。
EN: Please pay this bill in dollars.

ZH: 这项工程的成本超过了五千美元。
EN: The cost of this project exceeded five thousand dollars.

ZH: 我们拿着几百美元去购物。
EN: We went shopping with a few hundred dollars.

ZH: 这个广告费用将花费一万元美元。
EN: This advertisement will cost ten thousand dollars.

ZH: 他在邮局换了一百美元。
EN: He exchanged a hundred dollars at the post office.
